.\" template from man 7 groff_mdoc
.Dd June 28, 2012
.Dt LAZYLPSOLVERLIBS 1 "lazylpsolverlibs manual"
.Os @PACKAGE_VERSION@
.Sh NAME
.Nm lazyglpk_test
.Nd helper program to configure lazylpsolverlibs to work with glpk
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm lazyglpk_test
.Sh DESCRIPTION
This program will solve try to solve a linear program with glpk.  Success
indicates that the solver is correctly configured to work with
lazylpsolverlibs. Failure indicates that the solver was not found or could
not be interacted with.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables are used.
.Bl -tag -width ".." -compact
.Pp
.It Cm LAZLPSOLVERLIBS_GLPK_LIB
Interpreted as the full path to glpk library.
.Pp
.It Cm LAZLPSOLVERLIBS_DEBUG
If non empty, enables debug output on stdout.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width ".." -compact
.Pp
.It Cm /usr/lib/libglpk.so
This file is always checked first as a candidate for glpk library. It
takes precedence over the variable LAZLPSOLVERLIBS_GLPK_LIB. You should
symlink this file to the actual solver library.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The exit status is 0 if the solver is correctly configured and 1 otherwise.
.Sh SEE ALSO
lazygurobi_test(1) lazyxprs_test(1) lazycplex_test(1)
